Yeah, a function has to state when it wants the output. Example:[code:23617rpa]define function &lt;add&gt;
set &lt;num1; $parameter&#40;1&#41;$&gt;
set &lt;num2; $parameter&#40;2&#41;$&gt;
set numeric &lt;total; %num1% + %num2%&gt;
return &lt;%total%&gt;
set &lt;num1; 0&gt;
set &lt;num2; 0&gt;
end define[/code:23617rpa]The 'return' script tells it what to be in an expression such as &lt;5 - $add(2; 6)$&gt;. This example would be 5 - (2 + 6 ) = 5 - 8 = -3. Do you understand?

